This place has been rightly described as "the best 'Jersey-style' Italian restaurant in DC.” It has a simple menu that covers all the basics: pasta with marinara sauce +/- meatballs, meat sauce, an Alfredo dish, lasagna, chicken and veal dishes, and very decent pizzas, plus daily specials that include steak, seafood, and other not-necessarily-Italian items. Portions are large enough to make a meal by sharing a salad and one entree with a friend. The quality is consistently good. Their red sauce is very satisfying and reminds me of my own grandmother's. The restaurant is at street level, and has a small bar. Inside, the restaurant is not very large...maybe 15 tables...but there’s an outside patio that’s full when the weather is nice. Upstairs (same owners) is a fun neighborhood gay bar, where everyone (of legal age) is welcome, and where you can also order anything from the restaurant menu.
